choices.text:
spending a lot of money on mobile phone bill, that's the reason I decided to use Skype to call people from United Kingdom to Indonesia. The answer is a long story, tonight I'm going to tell you about my journey in using Skype to make cheap international calls.

Actually, there's another tutorial of skype about making cheaper internet call, but that tutorial is kind of old for some reasons (the pictures on the tutorial doesn't match the current version on Skype). if you are newbie, you might confuse when you try to config your written tutorial manually. The old skype tutorial is about video call as cheap alternative phone call. maybe if you are using a lot of webcam during a video call, you can enjoy free internet call. Ok, back to the main idea.

Here's description when I first used Skype:

try via BT internet connection, and soon my internet provider will send me a new router, so I have to disconnect my computer with the router every time. Then I start trying to use WiFi connection, and it turns out Skype doesn't like WiFi. Sometimes Skype can make a 2-way-communication and generate a sound from speaker to headset. But the other way around would be a complete silent.

Then I start exploring with my Laptop and internal microphone / speaker. it works!

I found several solutions that works fine in different network environments.
